metadata.name: 🟧🟦 QT 🟦🟧 #52
metadata.description:
🟧🟦 Qt is a unique interactive PFP.

🔶As you move the mouse, QT eyes monitor your movements and react accordingly. If you're lucky enough to have laser eyes, you have a QT protecting you. There are several gift hearts and diamonds around you that you can pick up(There is no doubt that you will use them somewhere.). Your QTs bring nouns and behavioral adjectives with them. In the gift that's going around the platform, you'll find it.

A total of thirty rare groups are considered for QTs, making them unique among PFPs and allowing you to have diverse and exclusive QTs.

🔷QT is not just an NFT. To make significant events more enjoyable, QT is with you. All you need to do is own QTs and follow them. You will be surprised by QTs. 1011 girls and 1011 boys will mint in the first series of QTs in 2022. At the opening of the 2022 World Cup, the first QT Boy pieces were minted.

🤝Saleh.C4d and  ArashMP collaborated on QT.

✅ you can save the image in the following sizes:

⌨️ Key number 1️⃣ 1080 pixels

⌨️ Key number 2️⃣ 216  pixels

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #3797
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: ðolmen #20
metadata.description:
ðolmen is a generative art project by Diego Pintos.
It draws rectangles with points instead a plain color or border. With some variations in the distribution of this points, we get a kind of noise depth effect.

12 carefully selected palettes. Based in Art Masterpieces and in Nature.
· Gioconda (Leonardo da Vinci)
· Guernika (Pablo Picasso)
· Nighthawks (Edward Hopper)
· Meninas (Diego Velazquez)
· Judith beheading Holofernes (Caravaggio)
· Al Siq (nature)
· guacamayo (nature)
· Salamanca (nature)
· mostaza (nature)
· Timanfaya (nature)
· piedra (nature)
· firefall (nature)

ðolmen builds 10 compositions:
· Square
· PersonChen's Style
· Equilibrium
· Hanging
· Pyramid
· Row
· Column
· 3 columns (randomly aligned)
· 3 rows (randomly aligned)
· Frame

Density
· Tiny: Less than 35 rects. Rare
· Small: Less than 100 rects. Common.
· Medium: Less than 250 rects. Common.
· High: Less than 350 rects. Common.
· Massive: Less than 500 rects. Rare.
· Ultra: More than 500 rects. Rarest.

Rarities
· Rectangle filling type: Filled (95%) or unfilled (5%)
· Monochrome: Just black and white. Always unfilled. (1%)
· Dark mode: Dark background (20%). Dark mode can be monochrome.
· Habitable (90%). See humans later.

Humans
ðolmen can host tiny humans. Contains a little code that draws humans looking down, in order to to provide size perspective.

Minting
Each ðolmen contains all rarities inside. As a ðolmen collector, you can display your final piece in all available formats, and rarity owners can display the regular filled composition. In addition, this can help if you want to print one or more formats.

Tricks and Keys
ðolmen is responsive, you can zoom out your browser window and refresh to get a larger output.
's' save the current canvas
'd' toggle dark mode
'f' toggle fill mode
'm' toggle monochrome

More info and visual description:
https://thelirios.com/dolmen/

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Harmonium #121
metadata.description:
I do not know which to prefer,
The beauty of inflections
Or the beauty of innuendoes,
The blackbird whistling
Or just after.

  Thirteen Ways of Looking at a Blackbird
  Wallace Stevens

Harmonium began as an algorithmic exploration of space filling and curve placement, and grew into a study of the many ways that forms can coexist in a space.

There are three stages to the rendering process:
1. Initial drawing with a placeholder color assignment algorithm
2. Analysis and final color assignment
3. Streamline tapering and conversion to SVG

The final step will typically cause the image to look darker than the previous steps due to the tapering of the streamlines and the vector nature of SVG. I recommend viewing Harmonium outputs on the largest screen you have available.

The final SVG version of the image can be exported by pressing the 'e' key.

*Plotting*

You can disable/enable streamline tapering by pressing the 't' key. Un-tapered exports are intended for plotting on your favorite pen plotter, and include several Inkscape-compatible layer definitions to make plotting different colors possible. (Be sure to disable the background layer.)

The SVG has no dimensions defined so you will need to set the paper dimensions by adjusting the SVG as needed. I will provide additional detail on how to do this in an upcoming blog post. (The short version is to change the page dimensions in Inkscape and set the viewbox width and height to 1.0.)

jpalmer.dev
@jeffpalmer

metadata.name: Kinetic Bug #198
metadata.description:
Best viewed on a decent GPU,  because physics simulations are performance intensive. Otherwise you might encounter a bug...

In a world of digital data, a new life is born. We are not alone...
Explore how kinetic bugs make their way through the world. What will their destiny be?
It's curious that we can sympathize to a predefined creature living it's predestined life in the digital world. Coding in the computer abyss reveals interesting worlds.

Keyboard
[ space ] - jump
[ click ] - increase velocity briefly
[ r ] - restart simulation
[ s ] - save image
[ f ] - full screen

Mobile
[ two finger tap ] - jump
[ tap ] - increase velocity briefly
